articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, James Mackenzie
articles.description: Israeli airstrikes killed at least six Palestinians guarding aid trucks against looters, Hamas officials said on Friday, underlining the problems hindering supplies from reaching hungry people in Gaza following Israel's 11-week-long blockade.
articles.title: Israeli strikes kill Palestinians protecting Gaza aid trucks, Hamas says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Friday that a major prisoner swap was just completed between Russia and Ukraine.
articles.title: Trump says major prisoner swap completed between Russia-Ukraine

articles.author: Parisa Hafezi, John Irish
articles.description: Iranian and U.S. negotiators will resume talks on Friday in Rome to resolve a decades-long dispute over Tehran's nuclear ambitions, despite Iran's supreme leader warning that clinching a new deal might be insurmountable amid clashing red lines.
articles.title: US and Iran to hold nuclear talks amid clashing red lines

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu accused the leaders of France, Britain and Canada of wanting to help the Palestinian militant group Hamas after they threatened to take "concrete action" if Israel did not stop its latest offensive in Gaza.
articles.title: Netanyahu accuses France, Britain and Canada of 'emboldening' Hamas

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Bangladesh's de-facto prime minister has threatened to step down if political parties cannot agree on reforms that citizens await with growing impatience, a top student leader has said, deepening uncertainty in the wake of deadly protests last year.
articles.title: Bangladesh's Yunus could quit over lack of reform progress, student leader says

articles.author: Panu Wongcha-Um
articles.description: Thailand will advocate more international engagement with Myanmar at an upcoming Southeast Asia leader summit next week, its foreign minister said, in a push for international cooperation to broaden a diplomatic effort to end a protracted civil war.
articles.title: Thailand to press for broader international engagement with Myanmar junta

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Tanzania has released the second of two foreign activists who had come to support an opposition leader charged with treason, her organisation said on Friday, after a Kenyan fellow activist said they had both been badly tortured.
articles.title: Tanzania releases Ugandan activist at border, Kenyan colleague alleges torture

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Sweden's security service said on Friday it had lowered the national threat assessment by one notch to "elevated" from "high", citing a gradual change in the overall situation.
articles.title: Sweden lowers national threat level

articles.author: Charlotte Van Campenhout
articles.description: Princess Elisabeth, the 23-year-old future queen of Belgium, has just completed her first year at Harvard University but the ban imposed by U.S. President Donald Trump's administration on foreign students studying there could jeopardise her continued studies.
articles.title: Future queen of Belgium caught up in Harvard foreign student ban

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's foreign ministry on Friday urged the Philippines to immediately stop "infringement and provocation" in the South China Sea or face China's "resolute response."
articles.title: China urges Philippines to stop provocation in South China Sea
